{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, the sam-pling policy exploits the structure underlying the domain to direct the queries in locations where a sample can represent a large amount of neighbouring samples. 3.",
    "Diversity estimates how well the queries are disseminated over the domain of samples.",
    "This is reflected in a sampling policy that selects samples scattering across the full domain, and prevents the concentration of queries in small local regions.Figure 3 illustrates a watering optimization problem that attempts to clarify the peculiarities of each learning criteria.",
    "This simple toy problem requires identifying the areas of a wheat field where the crop is ripe and where it is still unripe for irrigation purposes.",
    "The learning goal is formalized as the identification of the area where the wheat is lower, which means an unripe cultivation and maximum requirements for irrigation."
  ]
}